title: Bellevue beats North Cedar
text:
Bellevue beats North Cedar HERALD STAFF REPORT The Clinton Herald 
STANWOOD — Bellevue bounced back after North Cedar returned the opening kickoff for a touchdown and won the Class 1A District 5 football game 37-20 on Friday night. 
The win was the first for the Comets (2-4, 1-3 district) since opening night and dropped the Knights to 0-6, 0-3. 
North Cedar was on the scoreboard just 16 seconds into the game after Ian Malaby returned the opening kickoff 95 yards for a touchdown. 
The Comets came back, however, and grabbed the lead before the first quarter ended. 
A 31-yard field goal by Jacob Rentz — his third of the year — put Bellevue on the scoreboard, then it went ahead on a 39-yard pass from Cade Daugherty to Neal Valant with 23 seconds left in the quarter. Valant finished the game with four receptions for 105 yards. 
Daughery connected with Peter Kilburg on a 21-yard scoring play in the second quarter to extend the lead. North Cedar pulled within 16-13 late in the half, but Bellevue put the game out of reach with three third-quarter scores. 
Daugherty completed 6 of 9 passes for 133 yards, and Lucas Anderson carried the ball 26 times for 110 yards for the Comets. 
Mason Lyons led the Bellevue defense with six solo tackles and two assists. He had one sack and 2.5 tackles for lost yardage. Jacob Holst and Cody Fields each was in on eight tackles for the Knights.
